Ⅰ. Scope of application
1. This Privacy Policy applies to all services offered by Print Master except for certain specific products and services. These specific products and services will be governed by specific privacy policies.
2. It should be noted that this Privacy Policy does not apply to services provided to you by third parties except for the sharing of information with third parties as agreed in Article 4 of this Privacy Policy and confirmed by you.
Please be aware that if you provide personal information to a third party when you browse its website or use its products or services, your information shall be subject to the privacy policy of the third party, and we shall not be liable for any legal responsibility, so please be sure to read the third party's privacy policy carefully and confirm your acceptance of it at that time.
Ⅱ. How we collect and use your personal information
Personal information refers to all kinds of information recorded electronically or by other means that can, alone or in combination with other information, identify a specific natural person or reflect the activities of a specific natural person.
Sensitive personal information refers to personal information that, if leaked, illegally provided or misused, may endanger the safety of persons and property, and may easily lead to damage to a person's reputation, physical or mental health, or discriminatory treatment.
The products and services we provide rely on some of your information to operate, so when you use Print Master, you will need to provide us with, or allow us to collect, the information necessary for us to use that information to provide you with basic services and better and better services. Based on the different business functions, there are two types of personal information we collect and use: information that is necessary to fulfil the basic business functions of the products and services and information that may need to be collected. Based on different business functions, we will collect and use two types of your personal information: firstly, the information necessary to achieve the basic business functions of the products and services and the information that may need to be collected, and the information necessary to achieve the basic business functions of the products and services is the necessary personal information, and if you refuse to provide it, we will not be able to provide you with the basic business functions and the corresponding services; secondly, the information that may need to be collected for the expansion of the business functions, and you can independently choose whether or not to provide it or authorise us to collect it, and we will collect it based on your authorisation We will process such personal information based on your authorisation or consent or for the purposes necessary for the implementation of the extended business functions you have chosen. If you refuse to provide it, we will not be able to provide you with the extended business functions, but it will not affect your use of our basic business functions.
1. We collect and use your personal information for the stated purposes in the following scenarios：
1.1. Registration and Login
Registration Login：
When you register and login to your Print Master account, you can create a user by using your mobile phone number or email address and we will verify your identity by sending you a verification code, or you can register and login by using your mobile phone number (or email address) and password, which we collect for the purpose of providing you with the Register and Login service. We collect your mobile phone number (or email address) and password (if used) to provide you with registration and login services.
Authorised Login：
Print Master supports the use of third-party accounts (WeChat, QQ, Apple, Facebook) to register and login. If you use a third-party platform account to login, you need to authorise us to obtain your information on the third-party platform (avatar, nickname public information, and any other information you authorise us to obtain) to generate a Print Master account that is bound to the third-party account, so that you can directly access your Print Master account. You authorise us to obtain your information from the third party platform (avatar, nickname, public information and other information that you authorise us to use) to generate a Print Master account that is tied to that third party account, which will allow you to register, log in and use Print Master and related services directly. After you have agreed to the authorisation, we will also need to re-verify and bind your mobile phone number to confirm the authenticity of that third party account and consolidate all data.
If you do not provide the information required for any of the above login methods, you will only be able to browse and use some of the Print Master functions and will not be able to enjoy all of the services; if you only need to browse and use some of the Print Master functions, you do not need to register as our user and provide the above information.
