unctions
1.5.1. Depending on the execution of the business function, each business function may collect your system privileges as follows：
1.5.1.1.
B
asic business functions：
Add Device：
When you use the device search, connect and print function, we will request your camera
permission and Bluetooth permission for searching and connecting to Print Master's printer. Due to the operation mechanism of the mobile phone operating system, the system Bluetooth function will force to ask for the location permission, so after applying for the Bluetooth permission, we will apply for your location information, including the approximate location and the exact location, in order to finally achieve the connection to the printer via Bluetooth.
Lite Editing：
When saving data, we need to get your storage/reading permission to save the content in the storage space.
Creative Editing：
You need to get your store/read (and album) permission to print using photos, which is used to insert pictures from albums for printing.
Check Printing History and Save Printing History：
You need to get the Store/Read permission to find the content saved in the storage space and save the content in the storage space.
1.5.1.2.
E
xtended business functions：
Scanning recognition：
We need to get your camera privilege and album privilege when recognising the information content of 1D code and 2D code.
Picture recognitio
n
：
When you use the picture recognition function, we need to get the camera permission and album permission, which can be used to take pictures with the camera and insert the pictures in the album for OCR recognition.
Voice recognition：
When you use the voice recognition function, we need to get your microphone permissions, which are used to recognise the voice content and convert it to text content.
Scanning：
We need to get your camera privilege and album privilege when recognising the information content of 1D code and 2D code.
2. Exceptions to prior consent：
2.1.
N
ecessary for the conclusion and performance of a contract between us and you；
2.2. Necessary to perform legal duties or legal obligations；
2.3. In order to respond to public health emergencies, or necessary to protect the life, health and property safety of natural persons in emergency situations；
2.4. Implement news reporting, public opinion supervision and other activities for the public interest, and process personal information within a reasonable scope；
2.5. Process personal information disclosed by individuals themselves or otherwise legally disclosed within a reasonable scope in accordance with the provisions of this Law；
2.6. Other situations stipulated by laws and administrative regulations。
3. Anonymisation
The information we collect about you will be anonymised in a timely manner by technical means. On the premise of not disclosing your personal information, we have the right to analyse, mine and utilise the anonymised user data, and to carry out statistical analyses of the use of Print Master's products for the purpose of possible third-party information sharing.
Ⅲ. How we use cookies and similar technologies
We, or our third party partners, may collect and use your information through cookies and web beacons and store such information as log information. We use our own cookies and web beacons in order to provide you with a better user experience and service and for the following purposes:
1.
For
r
ecording your identity. For example, cookies and web beacons help us to recognise you as a registered user of our services or to store preferences or other information that you provide to us.
2. To analyse your use of our services. For example, we may use cookies and web beacons to understand what activities you use our Services for or which Services are most popular with you.
While we use cookies and web beacons for these purposes, we may provide non-personally identifiable information collected through cookies and web beacons to other partners for statistical processing to analyse how users use our Services.
There may be cookies and web beacons placed by other partners on our products and services.These cookies and web beacons may collect non-personally identifiable information about you for the purpose of analysing how you use such products or services. The collection and use of such information by these third party cookies and web beacons is not governed by this Privacy Policy, but by the privacy policies of the relevant third parties, and we are not responsible for such cookies and web beacons.
You can refuse or manage cookies through your browser settings,
but please note that if cookies or web beacons are deactivated, you may not be able to enjoy the best possible experience with the Service, and certain products or services may not function properly.
