2.4. we co-operate with third parties to provide you with services related to print master's platform or other network services, and these third parties agree to take the same responsibility for protecting user privacy as we do;
2.5. other disclosures that are required by law, regulation or policy.
3. We will publicly disclose your personal information only in the following circumstances:
3.1. with your individual agreement;
3.2. Disclosure based on law: We may publicly disclose your personal information when required to do so by law, legal process, litigation, or mandatory requirements of governmental authorities.
4. Exceptions to obtaining prior authorised agreement for the sharing, transfer, or public disclosure of personal information:
4.1. those related to the fulfilment of obligations imposed by laws and regulations by the controller of personal information;
4.2. directly related to national security, national defence security;
4.3. directly related to public safety, public health, or significant public interest;
4.4. directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgement;
4.5. for the purpose of safeguarding the life, property and other significant legitimate rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals, but it is difficult to obtain the authorised consent of the person himself/herself;
4.6. Personal information that the subject of personal information discloses to the public on his or her own initiative;
4.7. personal information collected from legitimate publicly disclosed information, such as legitimate news reports, government information disclosure and other channels.
5. According to the law, the sharing, transfer and disclosure of de-identified personal information that ensures that the recipient of the data is unable to recover and re-identify the subject of the information does not constitute the external sharing, transfer and public disclosure of personal information, and your agreement is not required for the retention and processing of such data.
Ⅴ. How you manage your information and account cancellation
In accordance with the relevant Chinese laws, regulations and standards, as well as the common practice in other countries and regions, we guarantee you to exercise the following rights to your personal information:
1.
R
ight of enquiry
You have the right to access your personal information, except as provided by law or regulation.
You can access your personal data and mobile phone number information in your account through "Print Master -
Profile
- Personal Information".
2.
R
ight of correction
If you find that we have processed your personal information incorrectly, you can edit your profile information in your account by going to "Print Master - Profile - Personal Information".
R
ight of deletion
In the following cases, you may submit a request to us to delete personal information:
3.1. if our handling of personal information violates laws and regulations;
3.2. if we collect or use your personal information without your consent;
3.3. if we process personal information in violation of our agreement with you;
3.4. if you no longer use our products or services, or if you have cancelled your account;
3.5. if we no longer provide products or services to you.
When you decide to delete a certain item or items of information, you can contact customer service to delete them
（
app@qu-in.com
），
or
call customer service at 400-660-2205.
4. Right of revocation
4.1 If you wish to revoke one or more authorisations, you can do so in "Phone - Setting - System rights management". If you want to revoke all the authorisations of the Privacy Policy, you can do so by going to "Phone - Setting - Apps and Services - App Management - Print Master - Storage - Delete Data".
Please note that the path may vary from device to device, so please refer to your device and the instructions and guidelines of your system developer.
You may also withdraw your agreement by contacting customer servic
e
（app@qu-in.com） or by calling
customer service
at 400-660-2205.
4.2. When you revoke your agreement or authorisation, we will not be able to continue to provide you with the services for which you have revoked your agreement or authorisation, and we will no longer process your personal information accordingly. The revocation of your agreement or authorisation will not affect the processing of your personal information previously carried out on the basis of your agreement or authorisation.
5. Right of cancellation
If you decide to stop using your Print Master account, you can
cel your
account. This can be done in Print Master -
Profile
- Setting -
Delete Account
. The cancellation request will take effect as soon as it is submitted and confirmed. After cancellation of your account, we will stop providing products or services to you and delete your personal information at your request, unless otherwise required by law or regulation.
The data in this account cannot be recovered after cancellation of the account, and all rewards and levels in the account will be cleared after cancellation of the account and cannot be retrieved afterwards; except as otherwise provided by laws and regulations, your personal information will be deleted or anonymised, and it is recommended that you make a good backup.
After cancellation, your mobile phone number and third-party login account will be automatically unbound, after which you can bind with a new Print Master account.
6. Subject to the requirements of relevant laws, your close relatives can exercise the above rights of access, copy, correction and deletion of your personal information, unless you have made other arrangements.
7. Responding to your request
7.1. For security purposes, you may be required to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity. We may ask you to verify your identity before processing your request.
7.2. We will respond within 15 working days or the time limit set by law or regulation. If you are not satisfied, you can also lodge a complaint by sending an email to app@qu-in.com or calling our customer service hotline at 400-660-2205.
7.3. For your reasonable requests, we do not charge you in principle, but for requests that are repeated many times and exceed the reasonable limit, we will charge a certain cost as appropriate. We may refuse requests that are unnecessarily repetitive, require excessive technical effort (for example, the development of a new system or a fundamental change in current practice), pose a risk to the legal rights of others, or are highly impractical (for example, involving the backing up of information stored on magnetic tapes).
7.4.
I
n the following cases, as required by laws and regulations, we will not be able to respond to your request as described above:
7.4.1. related to the fulfilment by the controller of personal information of the obligations stipulated in laws and regulations;
7.4.2. directly related to national security, national defence security;
7.4.3. directly related to public safety, public health, and significant public interests;
7.4.4. directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgement;
7.4.5. where the controller of the personal information has sufficient evidence that the subject of the personal information has subjective malice or has abused his or her rights;
7.4.6. for the purpose of safeguarding the subject of personal information or other individuals' significant legitimate rights and interests, such as life and property, but it is difficult to obtain the authorised consent of the individual;
7.4.7. when responding to the request of the subject of personal information will result in serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals or organisations;
7.4.8. where trade secrets are involved.
Ⅵ. How we store your personal information
1. The personal information we collect and generate in our operations in the People's Republic of China is, in principle, stored in the People's Republic of China, and your personal information is stored in accordance with the storage period stipulated in the laws and regulations of the People's Republic of China, departmental rules and regulations, and so on.
2. The storage period is the duration of your use of Print Master or until Print Master is notified of the deletion of your personal information, and we will delete your personal information in a timely manner when you request the deletion of the stored information or decide to discontinue your use of Print Master and cancel your account. We will also retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, unless such retention is mandated by law. For example, the Law of the People's Republic of China on Electronic Commerce requires that information on goods and services and transaction information be retained for a period of not less than three years from the date of completion of the transaction, and that logs of user behaviour in connection with the Services be anonymised. The criteria for determining the foregoing period include:
2.1. to fulfil the purpose of the transactions related to you, to maintain the corresponding transaction and business records, and to respond to your possible enquiries or complaints;
2.2. to ensure the security and quality of the services provided to you by the Platform;
2.3. whether you agree to a longer retention period;
2.4. whether there is any other special agreement on the retention period.
3. After your personal information exceeds the retention period, the Company will delete your personal information or anonymise it in accordance with the requirements of applicable laws (if you are a minor, we will handle your personal information in accordance with the requirements of relevant laws and regulations after your personal information exceeds the retention period). If, due to special circumstances, it is not possible to delete it in accordance with the relevant requirements, we will explain this part of the matter to you.
Ⅶ. How we protect your personal information
1.
We take the security of your personal information very seriously. We endeavour to protect your personal information by taking all reasonable physical, electronic and managerial security measures and use our best reasonable endeavours to prevent leakage, destruction or loss of your personal information, including, but not limited to, SSL, encrypted storage of information, and access control of data centres. We also take strict management of employees or outsourced personnel who may have access to your personal information, including but not limited to adopting measures such as controlling access to information, signing confidentiality agreements with personnel who have access to personal information, and monitoring the operation of such personnel.
2. Notwithstanding the agreement in paragraph 1 above, please understand that due to the existence of a variety of unpredictable or existing technology can not be defended against malicious means, even if we have tried to take the necessary protection measures, your information may still be leaked, destroyed or lost. If you find that your account number or password has been or will be disclosed for any reason, you should contact us immediately so that we can take timely countermeasures to prevent or reduce your losses.
3. In the unfortunate event of a personal information security incident, we will activate the emergency response plan to prevent the security incident from expanding, and will promptly inform you in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations of the following: the basic situation of the security incident and its possible impacts, the measures we have taken or will take to deal with the incident, the suggestions you can independently take to prevent and mitigate the risks, and remedial measures for you. We will promptly inform you of the situation related to the incident by email, letter, phone call or push notification, etc. When it is difficult to inform the subject of personal information one by one, we will take reasonable and effective ways to publish announcements. At the same time, we will also take the initiative to report the handling of personal information security incidents in accordance with the requirements of the regulatory authorities.
4. In the event that we undergo a corporate merger, demerger, etc., your information will continue to be protected by the surviving corporate entity at that time, and we will notify you of this by announcement, text message, or other written means; in the event that our products or services cease to operate, we will cease to continue to collect your information in a timely manner and notify you of this by announcement, text message, or other means, and then we will delete or make your information invisible.
Ⅷ. Revisions of this policy
Our user privacy policy is subject to change. We will update this policy in a timely manner when the following major changes occur that may cause a substantial impairment or significant impact on your rights under this policy：
1. Our service model has undergone significant changes. Such as the purpose of processing personal information, the type of personal information processed, the use of personal information, etc.;
2. We undergo major changes in ownership structure, organizational structure, etc. Such as changes in owners caused by business adjustments, bankruptcy mergers, etc.;
3. The main objects to whom personal information is shared, transferred or publicly disclosed change;
4. Significant changes in your rights to participate in the processing of personal information and how you exercise them;
5. When our responsible departments, contact information and complaint channels for handling personal information security change;
6. When the personal information security impact assessment report indicates that there is a high risk.
The changed privacy policy will be notified to you through Print Master's platform announcement or other appropriate means before the revision takes effect. In such circumstances, if you continue to use our services, you agree to be bound by the revised Privacy Policy.
Ⅸ. Dispute Jurisdiction
1. The laws of the People's Republic of China shall apply to the signing, entry into force, fulfilment and dispute resolution of this Privacy Policy.
2. Disputes relating to this agreement shall be resolved through friendly negotiation; if the negotiation fails, the dispute will be submitted to the court of competent jurisdiction in the place where the company is located to resolve the dispute.
